==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin adj. ''[[caldo]]'' (hot), and the suffix ''[[-arium]]'', room or place.


===Noun===
{{en-noun-irreg|caldaria}}

# In [[w:Roman Baths|Roman baths]], the hottest room, with a plunge-pool. It preceded the [[tepidarium]] and [[frigidarium]].
# In modern spas, a room with a hot floor.